<subSubSection id="F096251FF67F2CF7BCB27F95E83311CC" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="8F580157AAF390C6DE55A785151DD76F" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B034A5565288C2BCFA08A722DE4643B7" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">
An additional relatively large 
<taxonomicName id="FFD8429485AE1D127B3BCFB8517978D3" class="Actinopterygii" family="Myctophidae" genus="Diaphus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Diaphus" order="Myctophiformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="09BD7EE5B794BEC6E8C337467E605CAB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Diaphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species of about 6.0 mm in length is observed in the Ichishi Group and will be described separately by one of us (YT). It also belongs to the 
<taxonomicName id="C96D49EA7315B91D25EA78CCE396F00D" baseAuthorityName="Brauer" baseAuthorityYear="1904" class="Actinopterygii" family="Myctophidae" genus="Diaphus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Diaphus splendidus" order="Myctophiformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="splendidus">
<emphasis id="7DC946C6367CC5C18BC4A14FC44F73B8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Diaphus splendidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
otolith group and is characterized by a relatively long and sharp rostrum, a high postdorsal angle, and the lack of a postdorsal concavity.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C085992660407F4AF9A8A0CB21893166" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">
<emphasis id="FA55AB305E2877FF227D763CA276EE89" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">
<taxonomicName id="0E5B1439D14B62B16D8620DE8A59C813" authorityName="Gilbert" authorityYear="1906" class="Actinopterygii" family="Myctophidae" genus="Diaphus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Diaphus garmani" order="Myctophiformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="garmani">
<emphasis id="A9D8CF4EF9303D7FBCD5BD842D0E2A06" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Diaphus garmani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Otolith Group after 
<bibRefCitation id="877F756DE8CDEAD6F9B52F4A57DF6F68" author="Schwarzhans, W" journalOrPublisher="Palaeo Ichthyologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" pagination="41 - 82" refId="B58" refString="Schwarzhans, W, 2013a. A comparative morphological study of the Recent otoliths of the genera Diaphus, Idiolychnus and Lobianchia (Myctophidae). Palaeo Ichthyologica 13: 41 - 82" title="A comparative morphological study of the Recent otoliths of the genera Diaphus, Idiolychnus and Lobianchia (Myctophidae)." volume="13" year="2013 a">Schwarzhans (2013a)</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
